(1720, 'help', 4, 'Gif tools help / FAQ', 1, 'text', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '<h3>How can I change GIF animation speed?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Go to <a href="http://ezgif.com/split/">http://ezgif.com/split/</a><br />\r\nUpload image and click "Split it"<br />\r\nAt the bottom click "Edit animation" button<br />\r\nThere you can adjust delay to make animation slower or faster</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>I tried to crop/resize image, but the animation is broken/flickering/missing parts, how to fix it?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>There are many different ways how gif images can be encoded and optimized, and sometimes imagemagick (the program that does the actual conversion behind the scenes) cannot understand them right.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Try to crop or resize source image again and select other method from dropdown:<br />\r\n<img src="http://img.exs.lv/m/a/maadinsh/options.png" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>"ImageMagick + coalesce" option will work on pretty much any image, but is really slow and produces larger files, so leave it as your last resort.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h3>I created image, copy-pasted link somewhere and now it says it''s not found. Why?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Ezgif is image manipulation tool, not a hosting site. Sorry!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All the actions creates awful lot of image files (many gigabytes every day), and most of them are never used again, so they are deleted every night. Save the image when you finish work to your computer and upload to a hosting site like <a href="http://imgur.com/" rel="nofollow">http://imgur.com/</a>.</p>', 'ezgif', 'no-left-right', 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, '', '', '', 1720, 1, 'active'),
